# ── Stripe (use TEST mode keys for local dev: https://dashboard.stripe.com/test/apikeys)
# DUPLICATE-BY-DESIGN: this `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` is the *SvelteKit BFF* copy
# read by `src/lib/server/stripe.ts` when the checkout endpoint mints
# Checkout Sessions. The Axum API has its own `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` in
# `backend/.env` (webhooks, billing portal, dunning). Both files MUST hold
# the same `sk_test_…` / `sk_live_…` so the BFF and API agree on which
# Stripe account they are talking to. Do NOT set the two halves to
# different keys.
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_your_secret_key_here
# Optional: embedded card fields (forms) only — not required for hosted Checkout
PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_your_publishable_key_here

# Pricing uses the database (pricing_plans.stripe_price_id), not these env vars.
# After creating test Products/Prices in Stripe, set price IDs via SQL or Admin → Plans.
# See docs/stripe-local-testing.md

# App URL (Stripe Checkout success/cancel redirects). Production: your real site URL
PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:5173

# Public Rust API origin for **server-side** fetches (blog loaders, sitemap, etc.) during `pnpm build` / Vercel SSR.
# Browser bundles use same-origin `/api` (see `vercel.json` rewrites) so visitors are not blocked by CORS.
# VITE_API_URL=https://your-api.onrender.com

# Set to 1 only when you need the real service worker while running `pnpm dev` (default: SW off in dev).
# Must match `svelte.config.js` / `src/hooks.client.ts` policy.
# PUBLIC_SERVICE_WORKER_IN_DEV=1

# ── Admin / Rust API (optional here — canonical file is backend/.env) ───────
# The SvelteKit app does NOT read ADMIN_*; the Axum binary does on boot to seed
# the first admin row. For `pnpm dev:api` or `cargo run` in backend/, copy the
# full variable set from backend/.env.example into backend/.env (gitignored),
# then set real values there (e.g. same ADMIN_EMAIL / ADMIN_PASSWORD as Railway).
# NEVER put production passwords in this root file — .env.example is committed to git.
# ADMIN_EMAIL=you@example.com
# ADMIN_PASSWORD=use-a-strong-secret-only-in-backend-env
